STATE OF CONNECTICUT v. DAVID M. ECCLESTON (14895)

O’Connell, Foti and Schaller, Js.

Argued February 14 decision released March 5, 1996 Steven C. Antignani filed a brief for the appellant (defendant). Leon F. Dalbec, Jr., assistant state’s attorney, with whom, on the brief, were Michael Dearington, state’s attorney, and Juliett Crawford, supervisory assistant state’s attorney, for the appellee (state). PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
